Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new caching strategy for network traffic, which is directly related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses an optimization-based analysis of the proposed caching strategy, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed caching strategy can be seen as a control system for managing network traffic, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions the security implications of caching, which could potentially fall under the scope of cryptography and security. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The proposed caching strategy aims to improve the performance of network traffic, which falls under the scope of performance evaluation and optimization.
